description: SOAP Web Services Description Language endpoint. Returns XML response indicating SOAP web service support. Content-Type: application/xml. Allows HEAD, GET, and OPTIONS methods.
notes: WSDL endpoint present but returns minimal content (empty or very small response). Indicates SOAP web service implementation. The actual SOAP service endpoint location not directly identified - may require authenticated access or be at root path. Suggests application implements banking/account-related SOAP services based on CSS references to 'accountInfo' and 'accountHolderInfo'.
